headlines.shortLinkText: San Diego has easy time with Northern Arizona in 79-51 win

headlines.description: Deontae North scored 25 of his career-high-tying 30 points in the second half and Portland State ended the game with 16 consecutive field goals to rally past Santa Clara 87-84 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Portland State hits final 16 FGs, beats Santa Clara 87-84

headlines.description: Deandre Ayton had 29 points and 18 rebounds, Allonzo Trier scored 20 of his 25 points in the second half and Arizona outlasted Alabama 88-82 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayton leads Arizona to 88-82 win over Alabama

video.headline: Alabama, Arizona battle for the victory

headlines.description: Tres Tinkle and Drew Eubanks each scored 19 points as Oregon State pulled away from Arkansas Pine-Bluff in the second half for an 85-58 win on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tinkle, Eubanks score 19 apiece; Oregon St. beat UAPB 85-58

headlines.description: Damiyne Durham had 19 points and three steals and Rickey Holden scored six of his 10 points in the final five minutes to help CSU Bakersfield hold on for a 66-55 win over Idaho on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durham, Holden help CSUB beat Idaho 66-55

headlines.description: Deshon Taylor hit all 10 of his free-throw attempts and finished with 21 points, Ray Bowles added 19 points and Fresno State extended its win streak to six with an 83-63 victory over Cal Poly on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fresno State cruises to 83-63 win over Cal Poly

headlines.description: Jovan Mooring shot 50 percent from the field and scored 27 points to lead UNLV to an 89-82 victory over Illinois on Saturday night at the MGM Grand Garden.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mooring scores 27 to lead UNLV past Illinois, 89-82

headlines.description: Mike Thomas and Drew Buggs scored 13 points apiece to help Hawaii pull away, after a slow start, to beat Division II Hawaii Hilo 82-64 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Despite slow start, Thomas, Hawaii beat D-II Hawaii Hilo

headlines.description: The James Madison-Richmond men's basketball game scheduled for Saturday has been postponed until Sunday at 2 p.m. due to inclement weather.
headlines.shortLinkText: Weather delays JMU-Richmond men's basketball game

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
